## When to use this component

Use the notification banner to draw attention to something important that has happened or will happen, or something that the user needs to do.

For example you could use a notification banner to tell people about:

* a disruption to the service they are using
* an important task that they need to perform soon
* an important change to the document they are reading
* whether an action they performed was successful or not

[EXAMPLES]

## When not to use this component

Only add a notification banner to a page if its message is relevant to that page. Use them sparingly to avoid reducing their impact. 

Notification banners should not be used within the body of a document. If you need to draw attention to content within a document use the Warning text or Inset text components instead.

Don’t use notification banners to tell people about the overall outcome of a transaction. To confirm that a transaction has been completed, use the Confirmation page pattern.

## How it works

There are 2 ways to use the notification banner component. You can use HTML or, if you are using Nunjucks or the GOV.UK Prototype Kit, you can use the Nunjucks macro.

